<HEADLINE>
<P>
POINDEXTER SENTENCED TO PRISON FOR ROLE IN IRAN-CONTRA SCANDAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Give me a break! Poindexter deliberately subverted the will of our elected 
government, the U.S. Congress. He did this for his own political ends and 
nothing more. 
</P>
<P>
These people involved in this Iran-Contra scandal committed acts that border on 
treason. It seems incredible then that the harshest jail term (in fact, the 
only jail term) is a mere six months. Isn't this the era when we're supposed to 
"get tough" on criminals? 
</P>
<P>
The judge feels that poor Poindexter has suffered enough in legal costs (Part 
A, June 12). It obviously paid off for him. 
</P>
<P>
And maybe less obvious, but surely apt: This looks convincingly like another 
case of rich, white men taking care of their own. From the President on down to 
the sentencing judge -- what a sham! 
</P>
<P>
Where is the justice when I can count on spending a few years in jail if I get 
caught taking drugs to numb my mind to this kind of hypocrisy. 
</P>
<P>
MICHAEL SANCHEZ 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
