Associated Press that Iran made the request through diplomatic channels 
Saturday, a day after five movie theaters in Istanbul and one in Ankara began 
showing the film. The official said the government was considering the matter 
and would see whether it was possible to edit out the brief segment lampooning 
Khomeini. In one scene, the police detective played by Leslie Nielsen punches a 
character that looks like Khomeini and reveals a spiked punk hairdo under his 
