<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST /LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: HOUSE APPROVES FUNDS FOR HANSEN DAM LAKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The U.S. House of Representatives approved on Tuesday a bill containing 
$272,000 for the continued development of a recreational lake at Hansen Dam. 
</P>
<P>
The House also approved language requested by Rep. Howard Berman (D-Panorama 
City) that directs the U.S. Army Corps of Engineers to apply the money 
exclusively to the development of a recreational facility at the dam. 
</P>
<P>
It also directs the corps to continue a dredging operation until the dam basin 
is fully excavated, Berman said. 
</P>
<P>
"This is another important step toward a lake at Hansen Dam," Berman said. 
"Restoring this recreation area remains one of my highest priorities in 
Congress." 
</P>
<P>
The financing, contained in the Energy and Water Appropriations Act of 1990, is 
now subject to approval by the Senate. 
</P>
<P>
In 1969 and 1980, floods brought in millions of tons of debris into the dam, 
burying the one-time 130-acre lake. 
</P>
