<P>
LOTTO ODDS TO RISE AFTER TODAY'S GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Today is your last chance to beat the relatively good, 1-in-14-million odds of 
winning a multimillion-dollar Lotto jackpot. 
</P>
<P>
On Thursday, the odds go to 1 in 23 million. Sticking to plans announced May 
22, the state-run lottery will shut down Lotto 6/49 after tonight's drawing for 
an estimated $25-million jackpot and replace it with Lotto 6/53 on Thursday, 
officials said. Players will not be able to buy a lotto ticket from 7:45 p.m. 
tonight to 9 a.m. Thursday as the lottery changes over its computers. Gamblers 
will still bet a dollar, or more, but will pick six numbers from 1 to 53 
instead of from 1 to 49. 
</P>
