<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: LAX OFFICER SENTENCED FOR MOLESTING 2 WOMEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A former Los Angeles International Airport police officer who admitted sexually 
assaulting two women while he was on patrol has been sentenced to two years in 
prison. 
</P>
<P>
Robert Julian Lopez, 32, made a tearful statement of remorse before he was 
sentenced by Los Angeles Superior Court Commissioner Irwin H. Garfinkel, Deputy 
Dist. Atty. Alan Yochelson said. 
</P>
<P>
Lopez, hired by the airport police department in 1984 and fired following his 
1988 arrest, pleaded no contest in April to charges of sexually molesting the 
women during two separate incidents. In both cases, Lopez ordered women to get 
in his patrol car and assaulted them. 
</P>
