<P>
Bob Gainey, former Montreal Canadien captain, was hired as coach of the 
Minnesota North Stars. 
</P>
<P>
Gainey, 36, is the 16th coach in the organization's 23-year history. He spent 
1989-90 as a player-coach in France but otherwise has no coaching experience. 
</P>
<P>
In 16 years with the Canadiens, Gainey had 239 goals and 262 assists. A left 
wing, he was voted the NHL's top defensive forward four times and was the most 
valuable player in the Stanley Cup in 1979. 
</P>
