<TEXT>
<P>
The Lady Keystone Open, an LPGA event, may be hit with a tax bill of $60,000 
from township officials of Hershey, Pa., who are challenging the golf 
tournament's charitable status. 
</P>
<P>
About 17% of the $1.1 million in revenue taken in by the tournament last year 
went to charity -- mostly health-care organizations. The remainder went to the 
costs of running the tournament. 
</P>
