bought the property in 1971, Mattel had been a tenant for one year, the suit 
says. It was not until after 1988 that H&amp;H learned Mattel used the site as 
a plastic injection molding facility, where it had used "various dangerous, 
toxic and hazardous substances," according to the lawsuit. Hawthorne-based 
Mattel could not be reached for comment. 
